    <name>quadrix</name>

    <categories>
        <category>Internet</category>
    </categories>

    <summary>Minimal, simple, multi-platform chat app for the Matrix protocol</summary>

    <description>
      <p>- No data collection whatsoever</p>
      <p>- Completely free, no ads</p>
      <p>- Does not support end-to-end encryption (E2EE)</p>    
      <p>- Integrated video-conferencing with Jitsi Meet</p>
      <p>- Desktop apps for Windows, MacOS, and Linux (amd64, arm64, armhf)</p>
      <p>- Mobile apps for Android and iOS</p>
      <p>- Push notifications on mobile devices with Firebase Cloud Messaging</p>
      <p>- Unique top-down messaging feed</p>
      <p>- Ideally used with a private Matrix homeserver (https://matrix.org/docs/guides/installing-synapse)</p>
      <p>- Open source on github (https://github.com/alariej/quadrix)</p>

    </description>

